&lt;p&gt;We are seeking dynamic, motivated and innovative qualified Staff Nurses to support the Senior/Junior Sisters and the Ward Team on the 21 bedded Emergency Surgical Ward/Surgical Assessment Unit. You will need to have a keen interest in surgery and be committed to deliver high standards of patient care, whilst maintaining your own professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will provide a supportive environment and mentorship. We are committed to professional developing our staff. Team working is an integral part of the running of our SAU. This is an exciting opportunity for an enthusiastic and motivated nurse&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be expected to work full time/part time whilst demonstrating the following qualities:-&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;• Strong organisational skills.&lt;br /&gt;• Be able to work using own initiative.&lt;br /&gt;• A flexible approach.&lt;br /&gt;• Team working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We always put our patients at the heart of everything we do and take pride in our unified team working ethos.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews to be held on Friday 27th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
